        <name xml:lang="en">Sodium I</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on literature and estimates. In case of sodium hydroxide (NaOH), part of the unreacted volume is released as sodium ions as a part of wastewater. The efficiency of the waste water treatment plant (WWTP) is assumed to be 90%. This means that 10% of the volume of sodium ions on the inflow to the WWTP is released to the environment. 22.99 g/mol is the molar mass of sodium (Na); 39.99 g/mol is the molar mass of sodium hydroxide (NaOH).</comment>
        <uncertainty>
